    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with **Tyler Soderstrom** (76.91) and **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21) anchoring the lineup, both benefiting from favorable matchups against Michael Wacha and Luis Severino respectively. **Soderstrom** earns the top spot due to a massive 10% park boost and a strong platoon advantage against Wacha. **Pasquantino** similarly thrives with a +15% SP skill adjustment and an assumed #3 hole placement, providing the ceiling we need to offset the tougher matchups for **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** and **Trevor Story**. **Corbin Carroll** remains a core start at 75.04; while the matchup against Brandon Sproat is middle-of-the-road, his inherent floor and the likelihood of him hitting third make him an essential play in our SB-starved pursuit.\n\nThe most challenging decision today was leaving **Alex Freeland** on the bench. Despite a solid 49.05 projection, he ultimately fell short of the efficiency required to crack a deep starting core, particularly with **Brice Turang** offering more consistency in the #3 spot against Eduardo Rodriguez. Meanwhile, we are exercising extreme caution with **Austin Riley** (42.89); facing the elite arm of Tarik Skubal, his score plummeted due to the SP skill penalty, confirming the optimizer\u2019s choice to keep him benched to preserve our game caps. We are also monitoring the \"Lineup Pending\" status for **Vinnie Pasquantino**, **Brice Turang**, **Corbin Carroll**, **James Wood**, and **Tyler Soderstrom**\u2014any drop in the batting order for these players could tighten the efficiency margins significantly. **Kyle Karros** and **Mickey Moniak** receive a notable boost from wind blowing out in their matchup against Brandon Williamson, though **Moniak** remains a marginal start given the negative platoon impact and his low spot in the order.",
